AXA Mansard, a global insurance and asset management firm, says it has opened another office in Ibadan, Oyo State, as part of its efforts to drive insurance penetration in Nigeria. The Chief Customer and Marketing Officer of the company, Jumoke Odunlami, described the new office as another demonstration of AXA Mansard’s commitment to drive the penetration of insurance in Nigeria by bringing services closer to the people. Odunlami spoke at the opening of the Ibadan office recently, according to a statement. According to her, growing the company’s footprint nationwide with offices and welcome centres is part of the company’s strategy. She said, “Our vision as an organisation is to move from being a payer to a partner of our customers. We understand that to make good this promise, we must stay closer, so we can always be there when our customers need us. “So, in addition to our continued investment in digital and technology to serve our customers, our network of offices nationwide are designed to give our customers a personal touch.” The Head, Retail Solutions Division, Adeola Adebanjo, said the opening of the office and others nationwide would help AXA Mansard support, interact and engage with its customers better. He said, ‘This location will bring us closer to our esteemed customers in Ibadan and its environs and beyond that, it will make insurance products available, accessible and contribute to driving penetration of insurance in Nigeria. “Our goal is to through initiatives like this increase the confidence of our customers to take on opportunities for progress, while we take care of the uncertainties that come with life on their behalf.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com